##Hubei listed companies'anxiety about returning to work: Some can not stop, some can not afford to pay

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

The 112 listed companies that accounted for about a fifth of Hubei's GDP in the first half of 2019 are now coming back to work in different ways. Some companies have little impact, but there is also a large decline in corporate income risk

From Caijing, Wayne Wang, Xinpei Liu Yiqin

Editor Lu Ling

March 16, "CAIJING" reporters at the 688089.Sh (Jia biyou) site to see that the factory has been started, there are employees in and out. "I came to work on March 9, and half of the employees in my department were on the job, " An employee of the company's Fermentation Line told Caijing.

Jia biyou the above scene, Hubei announced since the resumption of some enterprises back to production in miniature.

As the national epidemic of new pneumonia has been effectively controlled, Zhejiang and other places in February to start an orderly resumption of work. As a major disaster area, the number of newly confirmed cases of pneumonia in Hubei Province gradually dropped to 4 cases on March 15, and achieved progress. Before this a few days, Hubei already pulled to resume work prologue.

On March 10, while inspecting the work of epidemic prevention and control in Wuhan, Hubei Province, Xi pointed out that on the premise of strengthening prevention and control, differentiation strategies should be adopted, and timely division and classification, classification and time division, conditional resumption of work and production should be initiated.

The next day, the COVID-19 issued a circular ("circular") : The province as a unit to the county, divided into low, medium and high risk areas, the implementation of differentiated prevention and control of the division level, conditional resumption of work and production when enterprises are classified and classified. "PEOPLE IN MEDIUM-AND LOW-RISK AREAS: By virtue of the Health Code Green Code, the province's safe and orderly flow; passenger flights, passenger trains and other traffic in the province are gradually and orderly restored. "

At present, how about the resumption of work in Hubei Enterprises?

CAIJING reporters found that in the first half of 2019, accounting for about one-fifth of Hubei Province's GDP, 112 listed companies in the province, the current resumption of work varies. Part of the epidemic prevention and control, major people's livelihood, agricultural supplies during the normal operation of enterprises during the epidemic.

"The company is one of the key chemical enterprises, and the cost of restarting some of the equipment after it is stopped production is very high, and some of the equipment is scrapped after it is stopped production, so production can not be suspended, " Xingfa Group (600141.Sh ) , which is located in Yichang, Hubei Province, told CAIJING, the production of agricultural materials such as glyphosate and ammonium phosphate has been running.

With the hing fat group in the "stop" list of enterprises, as well as Ogilvy and mather (Url) , in the 000759.sz  Group () and so on.

After the epidemic situation in Hubei has been effectively controlled, part of the key industrial chain supporting enterprises, enterprises undertaking major national, provincial and municipal projects and key projects will first be authorized to resume production.

As one of the three pillar industries in Hubei, the auto industry has taken the lead in resuming production, with the daily capacity of Dongfeng trucks in Shiyan reaching more than 200 units.

Yongan Pharmaceutical (002365.SZ ) , located in Qianjiang, Hubei Province, is the focus of the local resumption of work. Its application for resumption of work was approved on the evening of March 6. "The traffic blockade has been lifted, and the local employees have basically arrived at their posts, " a company official told Caijing. "The production problem has been solved. Everything else is easy to say. ".

Compared with other areas in Hubei Province, Wuhan, the center of the epidemic, is still strict in the management of resuming work and production. Except for key companies, other enterprises will resume work and production no earlier than 24:00 on March 20.

According to "CAIJING" reporters understand, real estate and other industries are not yet in the list of Wuhan resume work.

"We are not in the list to resume work, the offline sales business can not be carried out, the company has no new income. " A real estate staff in Wuhan, "CAIJING" reporters helpless said, the chief financial officer to jump.

Because the banking business can not handle, also has the real estate company to suspend the payment staff wages.

At present, the traffic arteries to Hubei Province, such as flights, high-speed Rail, passenger transport, have not been restored, and the non-provincial personnel can not return to work is still the main problem faced by local enterprises. Wuhan, the only high-risk area in Hubei Province as of March 14, is still under lockdown, with traffic problems particularly evident.

CAIJING reporter found that this round of the epidemic on Hubei listed companies in the first quarter of the impact of mixed. Some companies have little impact, but there is also a large decline in corporate income risk.

Grading, classification, orderly progression

In Hubei Province after the announcement of resumption of work, the central area of the epidemic in Hubei listed companies, the current resumption of work?

CAIJING reporters interviewed a number of listed companies in Hubei found that some of the key livelihood, important industry companies, in the epidemic period did not stop operations.

In the eye of the storm in Wuhan, the agricultural market all closed, the business supernatural has become the main channel of vegetable supply. Wuhan state-owned Group (000759.Sz ) , as a first-line security for the business super enterprise, guarding the Wuhan residents of the "basket. ".

Zhongbai Group relevant responsible person told the "finance and Economics" reporter, the company basically did not stop work, staff on-the-job rate of more than 90% . Since the city was closed on January 23, in addition to the closure of department stores, part of the warehouse supermarkets, convenience stores stores to maintain normal business. "CAIJING" reporters understand that the supermarket is only open until 5 pm, and individual consumers can not enter, the supermarket only accept community group purchase.

Companies that were also active during the outbreak, as was 600998.Sh  , a local pharmaceutical distributor in Wuhan. According to the command of Epidemic Prevention, the company held an emergency meeting on the evening of January 21, organized part of the staff back to work, epidemic prevention materials procurement, storage and distribution and other related work.

"We've been busy since years ago. On New Year's Eve, we eat lunch in boxes, and there are thousands of people in the group, " Liu Zhifeng, the company's Securities Department, told Caijing.

Central China numerical control (300161.SZ ) , which makes large infrared temperature measuring instruments for epidemic materials, has received a large number of orders from local government departments since January 21, but the company has about 100 units in stock before the Spring Festival, it is difficult to meet the needs of a sudden outbreak of epidemic prevention. "In order to be able to supply materials as soon as possible, Chen Jihong, chairman of the company, posted information in the circle of friends asking for help. TPV and a chip company temporarily pried open the warehouse and rushed the materials to Wuhan, " Li Shelin, vice-president of Huazhong CNC, told Caijing.

This reporter learned that Chutian high-speed (600035.Sh ) and two domestic first-line display panel enterprises, Tianma Microelectronics, Huaxing Optoelectronics in Wuhan Factory also did not stop.

After the Spring Festival, the support Hubei Epidemic Situation Safeguard, the agricultural material enterprise takes the lead to resume production.

300041.sz  , which produces structural sealants used in construction of Engineering Board houses, was the first to open two production lines on February 6 in support of the construction of Wuhan Huoshenshan and Leishenshan hospitals, and resumed production four days later in all four places. Currently, the construction rate in Hubei is close to 80% , shanghai, Guangdong and Changzhou are close to 90 per cent open.

"The Xiangyang government also encouraged us to start work early. Some of our products are imported as substitutes, and we supply them to Huawei, Ningde Times and China CRRC. Considering the national strategic interests and the upstream and downstream industrial chain, local governments allow us to resume production as soon as possible, provided that we have good protection,"Hui Tianxincai's Dong Mi Zhang Hongjian told CAIJING.

In order to ensure the supply of agricultural materials for spring ploughing, Xinyangfeng (000902.SZ ) , whose main business is phosphate compound fertilizer and new type fertilizer, is also one of the early workers in Hubei Province. The three production bases in Hubei that ceased production during the epidemic situation were fully resumed with local approval. As an important production base of phosphate fertilizer for agricultural materials, the output of phosphate fertilizer in Hubei Province accounts for more than 30% in China.

In March, with the improvement of the Hubei Epidemic, on the national and global industrial chain supporting enterprises have a major impact, undertaking key projects of enterprises to resume work applications began to be approved.

The automobile industry, which is the first of the three pillar industries, is of great significance to resume its work. Headquartered in Wuhan, Dongfeng Motor Group has production bases in Shiyan and Xiangyang.

Dongfeng Motor Group, told the "financial" reporter, the company's two complete car factories in Wuhan was recently approved to resume work. Compared with Wuhan, there is less pressure to resume work at car plants in Shiyan and Xiangyang, and preparations are under way. On March 6, the company arranged 104 vehicles to pick up more than 1,600 employees in Fang County and other places to return to the city of Shiyan to prepare for the resumption of production.

603719.Sh  , most stores in Wuhan are now open, but do not accept in-store purchases, with orders coming mainly from online delivery platforms and community group purchases. A clerk at a good-quality store told Caijing that the main stores in Wuhan did not open for business until after March, and some stores were closed from 10 a.m. to 5 p.m.

"CAIJING" reporter noted that Hubei part of the non-urgent need to resume work enterprises, at present only a few business resumed production.

The main business for hemorrhoid cream and other drugs Ma Ying Long (600993.Sh ) , production and manufacturing, only part of the production line of epidemic prevention materials, such as Chinese medicine, disinfection products, most of the processing is incoming materials. "The full resumption time is still waiting for government notification, " a company source said.

Urgently looking forward to the approval of the resumption of work

Relative to the above-mentioned key enterprises to resume production, more listed companies in Hubei has not yet resumed work.

"Our current strategy is just to work online, customers can pay 1,000 yuan online to reserve a room, and then take customers to the site to see model housing, " Li Ming (not his real name) , who works in sales at Wuhan Real Estate Company Nanguo Real Estate (002305.Sz ) , told CAIJING, the project is expected to resume work by the end of March, with a formal resumption around April 15.

Li Ming's project, his Yuehua Mansion, is a high rise + Foreign House for Nanguo real estate in Wuhan's Yangluo Economic Development Zone.

"before the outbreak, the program received 100 to 200 groups of customers a day, about eighty per cent of the customers paid a deposit, and now only about 12 customers paid a deposit for two weeks of online sales, " Li Ming said, "there is no new commission because we can not take our customers through the formalities after we pay the deposit online, so we can only take minimum wage at the moment, but our revenue comes mainly from commission. "

Nanguo real estate owners for property rental and property management, property sales. In addition to medium-sized supermarkets, pharmacies and other key businesses to open, and the real estate projects outside the gradual resumption of work, the company's Real Estate Projects in Wuhan has not yet started. Property sales accounted for more than 90% of the company's revenue in the first half of 2019.

According to the circular, in the Wuhan region, except for those enterprises whose epidemic prevention and control, public utilities, people's livelihood and agricultural production must involve important national and people's livelihood, and those enterprises that have a major impact on supporting national and global industrial chains, which may resume work upon approval, other enterprises will resume production no earlier than 24:00 on March 20.

Apparently, Li Ming's real estate company isn't on the resume list right now.

With the same situation in the south, another Hubei Housing enterprises also failed to start.

"shareholders are worried, the chairman is even more anxious, but we have to wait for the notification before we can resume work, " a Hubei real estate enterprise official told CAIJING. "wages were suspended because they could not go to the bank to do business. "

Parts of the industrial park in Wuhan are also waiting to be told to resume work.

"We have seven or eight companies in the industrial park, including building materials, food, smart equipment, mainly private enterprises. Before this, there were meetings in Wuhan to resume trade, mainly involving people's livelihood, pharmaceutical and other enterprises,"Wang Qiang (not his real name) , a director of Wuhan Industrial Park, told Caijing, our Company in the industrial park is not on the resume list yet.

Similar to the above-mentioned enterprises, a number of Hubei listed companies have successfully resumed work outside the province, but when the provincial business restart, still need to wait for the notice of the government.

The production of Huaxin Cement (600801.Sh ) , which accounts for about a third of the company's cement output, has resumed smoothly at bases outside Hubei, where production has yet to resume. "Most of the company's projects in Hubei are concentrated in high-and medium-risk areas, with less business in low-risk areas, " a company official said, adding that the company's production base in Hubei is mainly east of Hubei and west of Hubei and is widely distributed, the resumption of work around the time to wait for specific notice of the relevant local departments.

Sante cableway (002159.SZ ) , which belongs to the tourism industry, has started to resume work since the initial stage of the epidemic. At present, some projects outside the province have resumed work, but the projects in Hubei Province are still closed. The company responded to "Caijing" reporter said that the company has five projects in Hubei Province, the resumption of work time needs to be based on the local epidemic control situation, there is no clear opening time.

Although there are still many companies in Hubei can not resume work, but the preparatory work has already begun.

"The company has worked out a plan to return to work in batches, and employees with private cars will be the first to arrive, " said Li Ming, a salesman at Nanguo real estate, anti-epidemic materials such as disinfectant and masks are also ready. "It's hard to buy masks, but the amount you can scrape together through various channels will last you some time. "

"sufficient protective masks are a prerequisite for the resumption of work. " The above-mentioned personnel of Huaxin Cement also told the CAIJING reporter that the company's major shareholders are located abroad, and that they had previously helped the company to purchase many masks from overseas. In addition to donating to Huoshenshan hospital and others, there are still sufficient masks available for the resumption of work.

The difficult problem of returning to work remains to be solved

All over the country has long been back to work or full return to work, but for the epidemic center of Wuhan, full return to work is still a bit far.

"I've been out of town for two months, the company has partially resumed work and I've been in a hurry to get back, but the applications I've submitted haven't been accepted. The Community in Wuhan where I live is still basically closed and it is difficult to go back,"a wuhan-based pharmaceutical company source told CAIJING.

According to the reporter's understanding, field personnel need to go through a number of processes to enter the community, including preparation of materials, submission of applications for returning to the Han, pending review and the issuance of final pass. "Our community basically does not approve, probably is to guard against the risk, " said the pharmaceutical company person.

In addition to cumbersome procedures, the examination of exceptionally strict application to return to the Han, the number of staff to work, traffic congestion has become the biggest obstacle to resume work in Wuhan.

"The biggest problem that affects our resumption of work is that some of the employees are still in road-closed locations and can not get out at all, " said a wuhan-based Xinli Tech official. Although the company has partially resumed work, it has very few employees. Huaxin cement personage also tells a reporter, the traffic in the province is not smooth, the employee returned post was subjected to certain restriction.

"Many of the stranded workers can not return to Wuhan, and they will need to be quarantined for two weeks after their return. They must be quarantined by themselves as long as there are migrant workers in Hubei, " a wuhan-based Youguang technology source told reporters, at present, the number of employees returning to work is less than 1 / 5.

Due to the special epidemic in Wuhan, some employees also chose to leave their jobs. "The families of several colleagues have stopped them from coming to Wuhan to work. It's a bit difficult to recruit at the moment, " Xu Zhengbing, CEO of Guanshanjue Culture in Wuhan, told CAIJING.

Part of the staff back to work blocked, but also Kyushu Tong, enlightenment environment (000826.Sz ) in the work of the front-line staff is very large.

"Due to the large amount of medical waste generated by the hospital every day during the epidemic, time is tight and the task is heavy, " said the responsible person of edification environment. "We are facing great pressure and challenges. " The team took a "three shift" approach to medical waste treatment, 24 hours a day non-stop.

The reporter understands, because Wuhan public transportation still is in stagnate condition, at present resume work personnel basically by the employee that has private car is given priority to. However, in order to solve the problem, some enterprises are using shuttle bus to solve the problem of staff commuting.

Traffic Jam on the one hand caused difficulties for employees to return to work, on the other hand, also brought pressure to the company's logistics. Hui Tian Xincai Dong Mi Zhang Hong Jian told the reporter that due to the implementation of the city closure measures in most areas of Hubei, the traffic has been blocked, the transport to the outside world has also been affected, there is the pressure of logistics delays, rising freight costs.

HNC, which employs about 700 people in the factory and currently employs about 200 in Wuhan and about 70 on-the-job Staff, faces a dilemma even as some employees clamor to return to work. "What if an employee comes back to work and probably can't go into the community after work, or there's someone else in the house? The cost of centralized accommodation is really too high. If I put 100 employees to work now, the hotel charge would be 20,000 yuan a day,"Li said.

"Due to the impact of the Spring Festival holiday and the implementation of the epidemic blockade in many places, the cost of labor and transportation has increased significantly, and the cost of production has indeed increased. " Kyushu Tong told CAIJING that raw materials are in short supply, some of the protective equipment is a little tight at the moment.

Andomai a (000553.Sz ) , which has been given a work permit to resume production, can only be partially restored. By suppliers only part of the resumption of work, slow impact of logistics clearance, raw material supply shortage, full resumption of work still takes time.

However, recently, relevant officials of the Hubei Provincial Transportation Department said that at present, all places have formulated plans to gradually resume public transportation trips. In the next few days, in addition to Wuhan, more cities and counties will gradually resume public transportation trips, there will also be more "peer-to-peer" , "one-stop" vehicles to escort workers back to work.

Wuhan has returned to work, but the number of workers have been limited, only part of the return to work. More companies are still anxiously waiting to get back to work. For many companies, the government still does not have a clear timetable for resuming work.

Xu Chunlin, chairman of education technology at Wuhan's Songda University, also hopes to resume work as soon as possible. "I hope we can resume work on March 20, but the government has not informed us what conditions are needed to resume work. "

Xu told reporters that the epidemic has reduced the company's revenue by at least 30 percent, or more than 100 million yuan. "The trauma of the epidemic is enormous. We have to find a way to survive. On the one hand, we have carried on the structural adjustment of the business, give up or get rid of some business, penetrate the business that has the hope of erupting. At the same time, we must cut down on expenses, save every penny, endure until spring flowers bloom,"Xu said.

"Our business has basically come to a standstill and there was basically no revenue in the first quarter. Even if the market takes time to recover after the resumption of work, cash flow in the second half of the year may be strained, " Xu told reporters.

However, the resumption of work requires not only the restoration of traffic, but also the restoration of public service facilities. "Even if the application is approved, if public services such as public transportation and catering around us are not restored, we will not be able to go to work normally, " Xu told reporters.

The impact on performance is mixed

CAIJING reporter found that this round of the epidemic on the performance of listed companies in Hubei different impact.

XINGFA group, which did not stop production, was not affected by the outbreak. "downstream customers return to work late to pick up the goods, the current company orders exceeded inventory. " A company source told Caijing that the company's shipping channel was not restricted because the company's products, such as ammonium phosphate, are agricultural materials, province traffic has green passage, plus a quarter is off-season, so the impact of less performance.

Although the income of Hubei Province was greatly affected in February, the company was not dependent on the income of Hubei Province, and its operation was not affected by the epidemic in the short term.

From 2016 to 2018, the company's operating income mainly comes from eastern and southern China. During the same period, the proportion of the company's business income in central China was 7.35% , 8.38% and 14.85% respectively.

Chutian highway, where many local workers stayed put during the epidemic, had virtually no revenue in February and March, compared with the companies. "compared to the same period in previous years, revenue has fallen significantly, " said a person close to the company.

Sante cableway also told the CAIJING reporter that at present, although projects outside the province have been opened one after another, in order to prevent the epidemic, all projects have adopted measures to strictly control passenger flow, and the time for the resumption of operation of projects within the province is uncertain, the first quarter's results are being put to the test.

In addition to some of the company's first-quarter results are facing a test, some Hubei housing enterprises are also facing financial pressure.

A staff member of Lucky Star shares told the reporter of"finance and Economics", affected by the epidemic, the company's sales business can not actually promote, income impact is larger, at the same time can not handle pledge business, let the bank to issue new loans is unlikely.

Hubei Province has also introduced support policies for enterprises affected by the outbreak.

In February, Hubei issued a notice that financial institutions should help small, medium and micro-sized enterprises affected by the epidemic to tide over difficulties by lowering interest rates and adjusting repayment deadlines Give Related Enterprise Employment Subsidy, reduce production cost, etc. .

The staff said the company has two loans due to apply to the bank for extension, has been approved.

Fubang shares (300387.Sz ) also told Caijing that during the epidemic, the Wuhan East Lake Donghu New Technology Development Zone Yingcheng municipal government company provided strong support to maintain normal operation and production activities, "At the company's request, Yingcheng will be stationed at the working group site to guide the production base to prevent the epidemic and coordinate the financial institutions such as banks to provide financing policy support during the epidemic. "

Kyushu Tong also hopes for more support from the government, such as low-interest emergency loans and lower funding costs in the circulation sector.
